<section class="blog-faq">

  <h2>
    Frequently Asked Questions
  </h2>

  <div class="faq-list">

    <details>

      <summary>
         □ FAQ1 :What is the best stone for a bathroom sink?
      </summary>

      <p>
        Marble remains the most popular choice
        because of its luxury appearance and
        wide design flexibility.
      </p>

    </details>

    <details>

      <summary>
         □ FAQ2 : Does marble require sealing?
      </summary>

      <p>
        Yes. Most marble bathroom sinks should
        be sealed periodically to reduce staining.
      </p>

    </details>

    <details>

      <summary>
         □ FAQ3 :Is quartzite better than marble?
      </summary>

      <p>
        Quartzite is generally harder and more
        durable, while marble offers stronger
        visual appeal.
      </p>

    </details>

    <details>

      <summary>
         □ FAQ4 : Can stone sinks be customized?
      </summary>

      <p>
        Yes. Dimensions, edge profiles,
        drain locations, and finishes
        can all be customized.
      </p>

    </details>

    <details>

      <summary>
         □ FAQ5 : How long does production take?
      </summary>

      <p>
        Production time depends on design
        complexity and quantity, but custom
        projects commonly require several weeks.
      </p>

    </details>

  </div>

</section>